Topics: Variables,Data types

Variables:
The Java programming language defines the following kinds of Variables:
1.Local Variables
a.Tied to a method
b.Scope of a local variable is within the method

2.Instance Variables (Non-static)
a.Tied to an object
b.Scope of an instance variable is the whole class

3.Static Variables
a.Tied to a class
b.Shared by all instances of a class

